## Task 4 — Security Groups

### Security Group Rules

![Security Group Screenshot](screenshots/security-group.png)

|Port|Protocol|Source    |Purpose                         |
|----|--------|----------|--------------------------------|
|22  |TCP     |My IP only|SSH — restricted to admin only  |
|80  |TCP     |0.0.0.0/0 |HTTP — public web access        |
|443 |TCP     |0.0.0.0/0 |HTTPS — secure public web access|

**Security notes:**

- Port 22 is restricted to a single IP address to prevent brute-force attacks.
- Ports 80 and 443 are open to all IPs so the website is publicly accessible.
- No other ports are open — unnecessary exposure is avoided.

